le. I want to refine OEROptionalAnonymous1Test to utilize observable custom targets instead of UINT8. I should consider testing the static methods, like getValue and getObject, but only on active call sites. Maybe the current test suffices, but since the dynamic engine can’t cover everything, the new test could demonstrate Method.invoke via side effects. I might need to import ASN1Encodable and use org.bouncycastle.asn1.DEROctetString and ASN1Primitive as well.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing test class functionality**\\\\n\\\\nI'm looking at the OEROptionalAnonymous1Test, particularly at the method that reflects on public instance retrieval. I see that the DEROctetString holds an encoded value. ReflectiveOptionalValue resets, and I need to ensure the object's wrapped value is the same as the encoded one while checking the invocation count. \\\\n\\\\nNow, I'm wondering about the static mutability in the test and if parallel execution is possible. I think Class#getMethod will correctly retrieve a public method of the nested static final class, and I might need to pass a derived type. However, I can't use direct reflection for tests due to constraints on dynamic class loading. I need an array for supported types without unnecessary complications.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Preventing constant folding**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about preventing native constant folding by using a method parameter instead of relying on constants directly. So, I could implement a method like `private static <T> T decode(OEROptional optional, Class<T> targetType)`, which would return the object from the optional. This keeps the constant intact but moves it out of the call site. I’m also considering whether to conditionally check using `System.nanoTime() >= 0`. This could add an interesting dynamic to the method, but I’m unsure how it fits in yet!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_Gqxfzj7zFSaS4wg5HhoK6tWc|fc_02bbd92d4b7f31a30169fbb5a4b17881a1a8fa032134f9fa0c\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcutil_jdk18on/OEROptionalAnonymous1Test.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import java.math.BigInteger;\\n\\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1Integer;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.oer.OEROptional;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.oer.its.ieee1609dot2.basetypes.UINT8;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class OEROptionalAnonymous1Test {\\n    @Test\\n    void getObjectInvokesGetInstanceOnRequestedType() {\\n        ASN1Integer encodedValue = new ASN1Integer(BigInteger.valueOf(42));\\n        OEROptional optional = OEROptional.getInstance(encodedValue);\\n\\n        UINT8 decodedValue = optional.getObject(UINT8.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(decodedValue.getValue()).isEqualTo(BigInteger.valueOf(42));\\n    }\\n}\\n\", \"newText\": \"import org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1Encodable;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1Object;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1Primitive;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.DEROctetString;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.oer.OEROptional;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class OEROptionalAnonymous1Test {\\n    @Test\\n    void getObjectReflectivelyInvokesPublicGetInstanceOnRequestedType() {\\n        DEROctetString encodedValue = new DEROctetString(new byte[]{42});\\n        OEROptional optional = OEROptional.getInstance(encodedValue);\\n        ReflectiveOptionalValue.reset();\\n\\n        ReflectiveOptionalValue decodedValue = decodeOptional(optional, ReflectiveOptionalValue.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(decodedValue.getWrapped()).isSameAs(encodedValue);\\n        assertThat(ReflectiveOptionalValue.getInvocationCount()).isOne();\\n        assertThat(ReflectiveOptionalValue.getLastInput()).isSameAs(encodedValue);\\n    }\\n\\n    