5e\"}}\n3814:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Examining coverage issues**\\n\\nI'm looking into a JaCoCo-covered class, and it seems the JVM coverage report is lacking line numbers. Maybe there's another coverage system not picking this up due to the source being unknown. I wonder if I need to cause a frame with line numbers by forcing Method.invoke from OEROptional$1, but it doesn't seem static. I could compare reports, alter tests to call `AccessController.doPrivileged`, and examine how JaCoCo interacts with metadata, though there's complexity here.\\n\\n**Exploring JaCoCo source options**\\n\\nI'm wondering if I can provide a source file to the JaCoCo report by adding `additionalSourceDirs`. However, the class file still lacks a line table, which is frustrating. I’m considering whether the library might have a multi-release class with the SourceFile set to Unknown. To investigate further, I think running `javap -v` could help reveal the line table's details. Let's examine this possibility more closely!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_02bbd92d4b7f31a30169fbb651195881a19bc44a2b7ad865d5\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-7ZhXWoqmX3NcUWypQ192Ks6buffJuOhHlY5sXQ1c9J8eLex8BNBYXBfm3Eq-NdH0byyDb7JJf029HEFVSpulKvTgKfptCx43lHZwlDE2ue0yhgLgJBy-eh-HBR36PmBlQ8l4PeFn2ySh3fVGkNVay7f-3UXPIAc7inm8SxNUGmXNzUxfvUtXVX8Y2Az1ZhwlhpXIt62VDFqPCpFvPV1AcyXQxyxq8F5c6HEOuV4cfiP7pvRD2iN0osIUgUrnfzcXJzk7rZ4BFxv8ryZqJgeMYWIDgOnF07vTSGoj1ukQgJ8QfT2R9mDYJNj54HVTks1vr0W04WF9RT_r7SH7m6DgTKpq-7dDNuDXkqbAGBTbuQCUnCQUGrf46b-XKS6z3bnbx4CpJKn1DILGyoaWvOhwWkdIzMmfFUiPm2QKIg0jPAaWgLC8oD9BkMMTOcawKM3V7P8sJdXTDGN8H606Il2YrXENqDcKL8yrB9QCsUe8wG6KyGS1YkAHHVzeboI5g7FtCvQ1ZBfM2sanY3X6FhWuJcuSBKBk5mC9_WVU-OOgo3BgG1Mb4G138N8JgeWB7LTZ5QCSeOq2dcCQyiVNpKfFV95fc8IzPhq6rYHUCzsGbHMGVtdJdGTuwBSjEKREfaxhA6hZOW49wocf6UJT8yjpTc7QzFcsxHofy9g7GdNTspxFywkTR6L_Re92uIuX9G3RFm6ow5sl