", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"./AGENTS.md\\n./forge/AGENTS.md\\n./tests/src/AGENTS.md\\n./COVERAGE.md:399:| [`org.bouncycastle:bcpkix-jdk15on`](https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java) | 1.70 | 0.0% (0/6 calls) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Bouncy Castle PKIX provides Java APIs for CMS, PKCS, EAC, TSP, CMP, CRMF, OCSP, and certificate generation. It supports parsing, creating, and processing PKIX- and certificate-related cryptographic structures on JDK 1.5 and later.</details> |\\n./COVERAGE.md:400:| [`org.bouncycastle:bcpkix-jdk15to18`](https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java) | 1.77<br>– 1.84 | 100% (0/0 calls) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Provides Bouncy Castle Java APIs for PKIX, CMS, PKCS, EAC, TSP, CMP, CRMF, OCSP, and certificate generation. It targets JDK 1.5 through JDK 1.8 and is typically used alongside a JCE/JCA provider such as Bouncy Castle's cryptography provider.</details> |\\n./COVERAGE.md:401:| [`org.bouncycastle:bcpkix-jdk18on`](https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java) | 1.77<br>– 1.84 | 100% (0/0 calls) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Bouncy Castle PKIX provides Java APIs for CMS, PKCS, EAC, TSP, CMP, CRMF, OCSP, and X.509 certificate generation on JDK 1.8 and later. It is typically used with a JCE/JCA provider such as Bouncy Castle to build and process public-key infrastructure and related cryptographic message formats.</details> |\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:682:                'org.bouncycastle:bcpkix-jdk18on',\\n./metadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/1.77/reachability-metadata.json:5:        \\\"typeReached\\\": \\\"org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.BouncyCastleProvider\\\"\\n./metadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/1.77/reachability-metadata.json:7:      \\\"type\\\": \\\"org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.COMPOSITE$Mappings\\\",\\n./metadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/1.77/reachability-metadata.json:17:        \\\"typeReached\\\": \\\"org.bouncycastle.j