nd on the local source, but that seems not possible. The Gradle Jacoco effective jar might be instrumented from the original with line tables removed. What if I compile the source as part of the test? It seems risky but focused. \\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about having a public test class outside the library packages but altering the stack trace might be limited. The dynamic tracker uses the JVM stack — that complicates things.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Focusing on active class**\\\\n\\\\nThe developer emphasizes focusing only on the active class and not broadening to unrelated matters, since changing the infrastructure could impact everything, which seems inappropriate. The user just wants to add or refine tests, so I might need to inspect the external wants for compile-time details. However, the current repo shows false coverage for all Unknown Source, including OEROptional. \\\\n\\\\nI’m wondering if the `StackTraceElement` hack could help, as the Reflection API might only report the stack frame without affecting the Throwable.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_5sIVjojmnAIdvRCy9FjnFxmh|fc_06f36e5b8945ce040169fbb86d0ca08193a11edce0913d9c78\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk18on/1.77/build/reports/tests/test/classes/org_bouncycastle.bcutil_jdk18on.ItsUtilsAnonymous1Test.html\", \"limit\": 100}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1776, \"output\": 688, \"cacheRead\": 45568, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 48032, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778104415808, \"responseId\": \"resp_06f36e5b8945ce040169fbb860f4f08193aa3b3baaeff31ae2\"}}\n4015:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering dynamic reports**