\"text\\\":\\\"**Reviewing Jacoco XML**\\\\n\\\\nI’m looking into the Jacoco XML after our recent edits. It shows that the `Opaque$1` class method is covered, so execution is achieved there. I wonder if I should mention that this highlights a limitation in coverage reporting. However, the user asked me to focus on the task. It seems I need to clarify that further test refinements won’t change the null-line report, but that might be seen as unacceptable.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_R2tlCQwe7mkCu3q5BCQgs5lB|fc_0ecf577e0df83e1c0169fbba87a8388192b457280fb6b1c8be\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcutil_jdk18on/OpaqueAnonymous1Test.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\", \"newText\": \"import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    private static byte[] encode(ASN1Integer value, Element definition) throws Exception {\\n        ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        OEROutputStream oerOutput = new OEROutputStream(output);\\n        oerOutput.write(value, definition);\\n        return output.toByteArray();\\n    }\\n\\n}\", \"newText\": \"    @Test\\n    void getValueWrapsFailuresFromInvokedGetInstanceMethod() throws Exception {\\n        Element definition = OERDefinition.integer(0, 255).build();\\n        ASN1Integer encodedValue = new ASN1Integer(BigInteger.valueOf(7));\\n        Opaque opaque = new Opaque(encode(encodedValue, definition));\\n\\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> Opaque.getValue(RejectingValue.class, definition, opaque))\\n                .isInstanceOf(IllegalStateException.class)\\n                .hasMessageContaining(\\\"could not invoke getInstance on type\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private static byte[] encode(ASN1Integer value, Element definition) throws Exception {\\n        ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        OEROutputStream oerOutput = new OEROutputStream(output);\\n        oerOutput.write(value, definition);\\n        return output.toByteArray();\\n    }\\n\\n    public static final class RejectingValue {\\n        private RejectingValue() {\\n        }\\n\\n        public static RejectingValue getInstance(Object value) {\\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException(\\\"rejected parsed value \\\" + value.getClass().getSimpleName());\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1401, \"output\": 1329, \"cacheRead\": 50688, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 53418, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778104951660, \"responseId\": \"resp_0ecf577e0df83e1c0169fbba7892408192ac9bcadc63a6d5a3\"}}\n4909:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Reviewing Jacoco XML**\\n\\nI’m looking into the Jacoco XML after our recent edits. It shows that the `Opaque$1` class method is covered, so execution is achieved there. I wonder if I should mention that this highlights a limitation in coverage reporting. However, the user asked me to focus on the task. It seems I need to clarify that further test refinements won’t change the null-line report, but that might be seen as unacceptable.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0ecf577e0df83e1c0169fbba7980888192ab45ee94e0014842\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-7qHjY1qYsToRZy5d8nBFWuUApS-AkcArHSopax6TzUidcpQpqNDYSrsK9pBG7PV6jWCCukWnH-K7dFAplnFoLkV72ncthWawvA713Up2GLRHlbGE_1bYYJ-ncAC7PR15AX8fx4dNr5SWlJHjws4YZm8MX8yoC4KZPcNb1vKE2Xtg2gDxCDVbOybCWgsnssQEhPeEMd6S8BLATqYfOjWMF_zD5L2ynGC41WEMMxI42kI8Yp3aft30JFDj22Td5gqV1pl5mi3Q0e3IfY